Job_Description:
About Us:
Gallagher is a global leader in insurance, risk management and consulting services. We help businesses grow, communities thrive and people prosper.We live a culture defined by The Gallagher Way, our set of shared values and guiding tenets. A culture driven by our people, over 40,000 strong, serving our clients with customized solutions that will protect them and fuel their futures.

As a member of our benefits and HR consulting team, you’ll help our clients - employers of all sizes, across all industries - build workplaces that work better.
Overview:
This position will play a critical role in providing (ongoing or custom) reporting, analytics and data-driven insights that support the effective design and management of our clients’ benefit plans. This role will collaborate closely with Financial Benefit Consultants and Actuarial Consultants, fulfilling both custom and ad hoc requests from our approved data warehouse platforms. In addition, this role will play an important part in developing book of business insights that further Gallagher’s reputation as a thought leader in the benefits market. As a key member of the Insights & Analysis team, successful candidates must possess strong technical skills and be strong problem solvers and critical thinkers.
Responsibilities:
Client & Prospect Support
Develop and deploy aligned divisional processes, templates and dashboards for bringing best-in-class data analytic solutions to drive improved decision making and business performance for our clients;
Support creation of ad hoc queries and deliver custom reporting / analyses and presentations using SQL, web-based query builders from approved data warehouses, Microsoft Excel or other analytic tools;
Work collaboratively with Financial & Actuarial Consulting and branch account team members to determine clients’ analytics needs and deliver meaningful and actionable reporting and analytics solutions;
Support key prospect targets with data-driven insights, as needed;
Work closely with Data & Insights Lead, as well as the Director, Insights & Analysis and other key stakeholders to develop, improve and build upon our toolbox of benefits-focused analytic deliverables across the division;
Support internal trainings of FAC teams – both divisional and regional – as well as supporting branch-level promotion of data & analytics services and capabilities.
Insights & Thought Leadership
Work with Data & Insights Lead to create and deploy a regular cadence of meaningful book of business insights and trends;
Support divisional marketing and thought leadership initiatives with data-driven Health & Benefits insights and trends from our combined databases in GBSInsider;
Collaborate with New Business Intelligence team to regularly update metrics in support of prospect opportunity analyses – including book of business data, as well as data cuts by industry, size and/or geography.
Technical Expertise
Work to develop and maintain expert-level knowledge of all GBS approved data warehouse platforms, learning coding languages and/or different dashboard capabilities, as needed;
Continue to build technical skills on core tools and platforms – both through informal trainings and self-guided learning;
Supporting large analytics projects from start to finish, as needed;
Work to develop strong data storytelling capabilities and use those skills to create and present compelling and actionable analytics;
Identify ongoing process improvement opportunities, and assist in the design, testing, documentation and implementation of process enhancements – also identifying opportunities for automation as they arise.
Qualifications:
Competencies, Expertise and Business Acumen
Excellent verbal and written communication;
Strong strategic thinker and incredibly collaborative – both with internal team members and other divisional stakeholders;
Shows interest and potential to be an excellent “data storyteller”;
Self-starter with superb research skills and a general mindset of curiosity – investigating key drivers and root causes in data;
Creative problem solver with strong critical thinking and analytical skills – collecting, organizing, analyzing and presenting significant amounts of information with attention to detail;
Feels comfortable in giving and receiving constructive feedback;
Strong interpersonal skills and ability to develop and maintain professional relationships with internal and external stakeholders;
Consistently meets deadlines, and works well collaboratively as well as independently;
Ability to sell the value of GBS data analytics products and services by illustrating potential impact to prospects and clients.

Customer Service and Business Strategy
Builds knowledge of Gallagher tools, systems and shared resources;
Consistently follows client service workflows to ensure efficiency, timeliness and accuracy of execution;
Is willing to go the “Extra Mile” to achieve results that benefit the client, the Branch and Gallagher;
Accountable for meeting timeline of key analytics deliverables with consistency and accuracy;
Is able to adapt quickly to a variety of circumstances, and change approach when necessary.
Requirements
Bachelor’s Degree in STEM or Business-related field, and 3+ years of health plan financial, data mining or reporting experience;
Data Science, Analytics, Mathematics or Statistics background preferred, but not required;
Advanced Excel and data analysis skills, including a working knowledge of PowerBI and/or SQL;
A quick study with interest in learning new skills, tools and data platforms.
